route groups ----> (folder_name) - Parentheses `()` me folder name rakhne se wo URL path me segment add nahi karta. - URL structure clean rakhne aur routes ko organize karne ke liye use hota hai. - Har route group ka apna alag `_layout.tsx` ho sakta hai jo sirf usi group ke screens pe apply hoga.

     Example:
     Agar humare paas ye folder structure hai:
     app/
     ├── (auth)/
     │   ├── _layout.tsx
     │   ├── login.tsx
     │   └── signup.tsx
     └── (main)/
         ├── _layout.tsx
         ├── home.tsx
         └── profile.tsx

     URLs aise banenge:
     - `app/(auth)/login.tsx`   ----> `/login` (not `/auth/login`)
     - `app/(auth)/signup.tsx`  ----> `/signup`
     - `app/(main)/home.tsx`    ----> `/home`
     - `app/(main)/profile.tsx` ----> `/profile`

     Benefits:
     1. Isse hum `(auth)` ke liye alag layout (jaise no tab bar, custom header) aur `(main)` ke liye alag layout (jaise tab bar nav) use kar sakte hain, bina URL paths ko change kiye.
     2. Group ke andar generic file names use kar sakte hain bina sibling routes ko affect kiye.

     Nested & Global Layouts (Important):
     - Route groups use karne ke baad bhi global/root layout (`app/_layout.tsx`) kaam karega aur wrapper rahega.
     - Global layout sabse top-most parent hota hai jo pure app ke screens/groups ke upar apply hota hai (e.g., Context Providers, Theme, or Global state).
     - Route group ke layouts (`app/(auth)/_layout.tsx`) global layout ke andar nest (embed) hote hain.

     Rendering Hierarchy:
     Root/Global Layout (app/_layout.tsx)
       └── Route Group Layout (app/(auth)/_layout.tsx)
             └── Screen (app/(auth)/login.tsx)

//==================================================================

Protected Routes (<Stack.Protected>) - **Introduction:** Expo Router v5+ (Expo SDK 53+) ka declarative component hai jo screen/route protection ko easy banata hai. - **Concept:** Bina manual redirects (`router.replace`) ya nested layout hook checks ke screens ko declarative guard provide karta hai. - **`guard` Prop (Boolean):** - `guard={true}` -> Access allowed. - `guard={false}` -> Access blocked, automatically redirect ho jayega. - **Key Features:** - **Auto-Redirection:** Agar condition fail hoti hai, to user anchor screen (usually index `/`) pe redirect ho jata hai. - **History Cleanup:** Logout hone par (guard changing from true to false), restricted routes navigation stack se automatically clear/remove ho jate hain. - **Deep Linking Safety:** Directly link open karne par bhi guard checks enforce hote hain.

     Example:
     ```tsx
     import { Stack } from "expo-router";

     export default function RootLayout() {
       const isAuth = true; // global auth state

       return (
         <Stack>
           {/* Unauthenticated routes */}
           <Stack.Protected guard={!isAuth}>
             <Stack.Screen name="(auth)" options={{ headerShown: false }} />
           </Stack.Protected>

           {/* Authenticated routes */}
           <Stack.Protected guard={isAuth}>
             <Stack.Screen name="index" />
             <Stack.Screen name="about" />
           </Stack.Protected>
         </Stack>
       );
     }
     ```

